It was excellent.
They say the trip was a "once-in-a-lifetime, 
unforgettable experience", so it was "excellent".

show someone - around town
pick someone up - at the airport
turn something simple - into something great

What was most surprising about the stay?
how nice the place was

The three texts in this lesson show a normal 
pattern for reviews. Usually negative reviews are 
short and just list problems, and usually people 
who write positive reviews like to add more detail. 
This is not a perfect rule, but it can be 
a helpful place to start.
If you need to write something in English, 
it can be helpful to look at a few examples 
to understand the patterns people follow to help 
you find the right style to use.


The negative review
This review uses shorter sentences and lists a series of problems.

The neutral review
This review uses linking words to balance positives with negatives.

The positive review
This review uses more descriptive language like adjectives, and tells a story.

