2.5 - Developing fluency Write an accommodation review

My experience at the Rou Hotel was rather disappointing.
The rooms were horrible and the area 
was very noisy at night.
* "noisy area" is the opposite of "quiet area".

The Espresso apartment had no air conditioning but the staff were very helpful.
The rooms are small and dark and there’s no air conditioning. But it's close to the centre and the staff were helpful.

The Espresso apartment itself is nothing special.
The staff were very helpful.
* amazing view / helpful staff / luxurious rooms / 
noisy at night / no air conditioning

Minka’s apartment is clean and the interior feels 
very luxurious. Plus, it has an amazing view of the sea.

The apartment is clean and the interior feels very luxurious.
I'm visiting friends in Istanbul next weekend.
* We can also say "I'm going to visit friends...".

The location of the restaurant was nice but 
the food was nothing special.
As soon as I got home, I put the shopping in the refrigerator.



















































